FBIS3-1493 "drafr061_a_94001" FBIS-AFR-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Burundi Minister Stresses Need for Western Intervention LD2903203594 Paris Radio France International in French 1830 GMT 29 Mar 94 LD2903203594 Paris Radio France International Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] In Burundi, the interior minister has called for the deployment of a buffer force of at least 5,000 men in his country. The minister has accused the Army of disobeying the government and of disarming Hutus only. He deems an intervention of Western countries as indispensable in Burundi.
